OL,3,CClimate scientist sheds light on
OL,4,Cextreme weather as report released
OL,6,F"When we think about climate change,
OL,7,Fit's not just something that's going
OL,8,Fto happen later this century, it's
OL,9,Fhappening already."
OL,11,FThe report explains that 2023 was the
OL,12,Fsecond hottest year since records
OL,13,Fbegan in 1884, behind only 2022.
OL,15,FThe number of "hot" days, designated
OL,16,Fas 28 degrees Celsius or above, and
OL,17,F"extremely wet" days are both
OL,18,Fincreasing.
