OL,3,CClimate scientist sheds light on
OL,4,Cextreme weather as report released
OL,6,FA few months prior in Jersey, flash
OL,7,Fflooding hit the Grands Vaux area and
OL,8,F22 homes were left uninhabitable due
OL,9,Fto the heavy rainfall.
OL,11,FPaul Aked, Head of Meteorology at
OL,12,FJersey Met, says: "The jury is out on
OL,13,Fwhether we're going to see these
OL,14,Fevents happening more often.
OL,16,F"But what we are saying, and this goes
OL,17,Fback to the atmosphere warming and
OL,18,Fholding more moisture, is that when we
OL,19,Fdo get extreme events, the science is
OL,20,Fconsistently saying we will see
OL,21,Fpotentially more extreme conditions."
